[To find Cahul province in south west Moldova on the Romanian border, go to: http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/commonwealth/moldova_pol01.jpg.

Anthrax is sporadic in Moldova, with just the occasional reported outbreak. Latterly, there was a bovine case in Riscani in 2012, none in sheep and horses, but 2 cases in pigs in 2011 in Orbei and Stefan-Voda, and a 3rd swine case in 2011 in Rezina. Or put another way, in spite of the claimed universal livestock vaccination, the occasional bovine case is not reported. It is butchered, and the farm pigs feed on the viscera and occasionally die; the vet is called, and anthrax gets diagnosed and reported. In this instance, it came about because of suspicious cutaneous lesions in 4, maybe 5 -- the account is a mite confused -- cases, and an alert medical doctor. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2748750,121.]
